title: Crispy Fried Chicken
summary: Crispy Fried Chicken might be just the main course you are searching for. This recipe makes 4 servings with 1249 calories, 69g of protein, and 67g of fat each. For $3.09 per serving, this recipe covers 38% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 1 person has tried and liked this recipe. A mixture of table salt, pepper, tabasco, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so delicious. To use up the brown sugar you could follow this main course with the Brown-sugar Pound Cupcakes With Brown-butter Glaze as a dessert. It is a rather pricey recipe for fans of Southern food. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 45 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 73%. This score is pretty good. winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sparkling Wine, and Zinfandel are great choices for Southern. In general, there are a few rules that will help you pair wine with southern food. Food-friendly riesling or sparkling white wine will work with many fried foods, while zinfandel is great with barbecued fare. The Pacific Rim Riesling with a 4.2 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 12 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Pacific Rim Riesling
productMatches.description: Portraying bright crispness, subtle sweetness and aromas of jasmine, pear and apple, Pacific Rim Riesling exemplifies the harmony of Riesling. The sweetness plays wonderfully with fiery fare (from Thai to Mexican), while the natural acidity stands up to richer foods (from French to German).
